---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Fourier Series — Math Explorations | Hayaan Dangra"
  description="Interactive visualization showing how any periodic wave can be built from simple sine waves using Fourier series."
>
  <section class="demo-page section">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Fourier Series: Building Waves</h1>

      <div class="explanation">
        <p>This one started when I learned that your phone breaks every sound into sine waves. Every song, every voice note, every notification — just sine waves with different frequencies stacked on top of each other. That sounded wrong to me. A square wave has sharp corners. Sine waves are smooth. How?</p>
        <p>So I built this. Start with 1 sine wave — it looks nothing like a square wave. Add another. And another. By the time you hit 10 terms, it's getting close. By 50, it's nearly perfect. The sharp corners are the last thing to converge, and they technically never do (that's called the Gibbs phenomenon, and it's still weird to me).</p>
      </div>

      <div class="demo-container">
        <h2>Wave Approximation</h2>
        <canvas id="fourierCanvas"></canvas>

        <div class="controls">
          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="waveType">Wave Type:</label>
            <select id="waveType">
              <option value="square" selected>Square Wave</option>
              <option value="triangle">Triangle Wave</option>
              <option value="sawtooth">Sawtooth Wave</option>
            </select>
          </div>

          <div class="control-group">
            <label for="termsSlider">
              Number of Terms: <span id="termsValue">1</span>
            </label>
            <input type="range" id="termsSlider" min="1" max="50" step="1" value="1">
          </div>

          <div class="checkbox-group">
            <input type="checkbox" id="showComponents">
            <label for="showComponents">Show individual sine components</label>
          </div>

          <div class="button-group">
            <button id="resetBtn">Reset</button>
            <button id="animateBtn">Animate</button>
          </div>

          <div class="stats">
            <p><strong>Terms:</strong> <span id="termsDisplay">1</span></p>
            <p><strong>Error:</strong> <span id="errorDisplay">—</span></p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="why-matters">
        <h2>What I Can't Stop Thinking About</h2>
        <p>When Fourier proposed this in 1807, other mathematicians basically said "no way." Lagrange — one of the greatest mathematicians alive at the time — thought it was wrong. The idea that ANY wave could be broken into sine waves seemed too good to be true. It took decades for the math community to accept it.</p>
        <p>What gets me is how universal it is. MP3s, JPEGs, MRIs, noise-cancelling headphones, your phone's signal processing — all of it runs on this same 200-year-old idea. Toggle "show components" with a few terms and you can literally watch the recipe come together. That's the part that made it click for me — seeing each ingredient separately.</p>
      </div>

      <nav class="demo-nav">
        <a href="/math-explorations/walks">← Random Walks</a>
        <a href="/math-explorations">Back to Math Explorations</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .demo-page {
    padding: var(--space-xl) 0 var(--space-3xl);
  }

  h1 {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-xl);
  }

  h2 {
    margin-top: var(--space-xl);
    margin-bottom: var(--space-md);
  }

  .explanation {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-2xl);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid #9B59B6;
  }

  .demo-container {
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  canvas {
    width: 100%;
    height: 400px;
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: var(--space-lg);
  }

  .controls {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-md);
  }

  .control-group {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .checkbox-group {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--space-xs);
  }

  .checkbox-group input[type="checkbox"] {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .checkbox-group label {
    margin: 0;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-weight: 400;
  }

  label {
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--charcoal);
  }

  #termsValue {
    color: #9B59B6;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  input[type="range"] {
    width: 100%;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 4px;
    background: var(--mid-gray);
    outline: none;
    -webkit-appearance: none;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-webkit-slider-thumb {
    -webkit-appearance: none;
    appearance: none;
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #9B59B6;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  input[type="range"]::-moz-range-thumb {
    width: 20px;
    height: 20px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: #9B59B6;
    cursor: pointer;
    border: none;
  }

  select {
    width: 100%;
    padding: var(--space-sm);
    border: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    border-radius: 4px;
    background-color: var(--white);
    font-family: var(--font-body);
    font-size: 1rem;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  .button-group {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--space-sm);
  }

  button {
    flex: 1;
    min-height: 44px;
  }

  .stats {
    padding: var(--space-md);
    background-color: var(--white);
    border-radius: 4px;
    border-left: 4px solid #9B59B6;
  }

  .stats p {
    margin: var(--space-xs) 0;
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .stats span {
    color: #9B59B6;
    font-weight: 700;
  }

  .why-matters {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: var(--space-2xl) auto;
    padding: var(--space-lg);
    background-color: var(--light-gray);
    border-radius: 8px;
    border-left: 4px solid var(--orange);
  }

  .demo-nav {
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    gap: var(--space-md);
    margin-top: var(--space-2xl);
    padding-top: var(--space-xl);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--mid-gray);
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }

  .demo-nav a {
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    canvas {
      height: 300px;
    }

    .demo-nav {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: center;
    }
  }
</style>

<script>
  const canvas = document.getElementById('fourierCanvas') as HTMLCanvasElement;
  const waveType = document.getElementById('waveType') as HTMLSelectElement;
  const termsSlider = document.getElementById('termsSlider') as HTMLInputElement;
  const termsValue = document.getElementById('termsValue') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const showComponents = document.getElementById('showComponents') as HTMLInputElement;
  const resetBtn = document.getElementById('resetBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const animateBtn = document.getElementById('animateBtn') as HTMLButtonElement;
  const termsDisplay = document.getElementById('termsDisplay') as HTMLSpanElement;
  const errorDisplay = document.getElementById('errorDisplay') as HTMLSpanElement;

  let animationFrame: number | null = null;
  let isAnimating = false;

  function setupCanvas() {
    const dpr = window.devicePixelRatio || 1;
    const rect = canvas.getBoundingClientRect();
    canvas.width = rect.width * dpr;
    canvas.height = rect.height * dpr;
    const ctx = canvas.getContext('2d')!;
    ctx.scale(dpr, dpr);
    return { ctx, width: rect.width, height: rect.height };
  }

  function targetWave(x: number, type: string): number {
    const period = Math.PI * 2;
    const phase = x % period;

    if (type === 'square') {
      return phase < Math.PI ? 1 : -1;
    } else if (type === 'triangle') {
      if (phase < Math.PI / 2) return phase / (Math.PI / 2);
      if (phase < 3 * Math.PI / 2) return 1 - 2 * (phase - Math.PI / 2) / Math.PI;
      return -1 + (phase - 3 * Math.PI / 2) / (Math.PI / 2);
    } else if (type === 'sawtooth') {
      return 2 * (phase / period) - 1;
    }
    return 0;
  }

  function fourierApproximation(x: number, n: number, type: string): number {
    let sum = 0;

    if (type === 'square') {
      // Square wave: (4/π) * Σ sin((2k-1)x)/(2k-1)
      for (let k = 1; k <= n; k++) {
        sum += Math.sin((2 * k - 1) * x) / (2 * k - 1);
      }
      return (4 / Math.PI) * sum;
    } else if (type === 'triangle') {
      // Triangle wave: (8/π²) * Σ (-1)^k * sin((2k+1)x)/(2k+1)²
      for (let k = 0; k < n; k++) {
        const sign = k % 2 === 0 ? 1 : -1;
        sum += sign * Math.sin((2 * k + 1) * x) / Math.pow(2 * k + 1, 2);
      }
      return (8 / (Math.PI * Math.PI)) * sum;
    } else if (type === 'sawtooth') {
      // Sawtooth wave: -(2/π) * Σ (-1)^k * sin(kx)/k
      for (let k = 1; k <= n; k++) {
        const sign = k % 2 === 0 ? 1 : -1;
        sum += sign * Math.sin(k * x) / k;
      }
      return -(2 / Math.PI) * sum;
    }

    return 0;
  }

  function drawFourierSeries() {
    const { ctx, width, height } = setupCanvas();
    const type = waveType.value;
    const n = parseInt(termsSlider.value);

    termsValue.textContent = n.toString();
    termsDisplay.textContent = n.toString();

    ctx.fillStyle = '#FFFFFF';
    ctx.fillRect(0, 0, width, height);

    const padding = 40;
    const graphWidth = width - 2 * padding;
    const graphHeight = height - 2 * padding;
    const centerY = height / 2;

    // Draw axes
    ctx.strokeStyle = '#ECF0F1';
    ctx.lineWidth = 2;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(padding, padding);
    ctx.lineTo(padding, height - padding);
    ctx.lineTo(width - padding, height - padding);
    ctx.stroke();

    ctx.strokeStyle = '#BDC3C7';
    ctx.lineWidth = 1;
    ctx.beginPath();
    ctx.moveTo(padding, centerY);
    ctx.lineTo(width - padding, centerY);
    ctx.stroke();

    const samples = 1000;
    const xRange = 4 * Math.PI;

    // Draw target wave (dashed)
    ctx.strokeStyle = '#BDC3C7';
    ctx.lineWidth = 2;
    ctx.setLineDash([5, 5]);
    ctx.beginPath();

    for (let i = 0; i <= samples; i++) {
      const x = (i / samples) * xRange;
      const y = targetWave(x, type);
      const px = padding + (i / samples) * graphWidth;
      const py = centerY - (y * graphHeight / 4);

      if (i === 0) {
        ctx.moveTo(px, py);
      } else {
        ctx.lineTo(px, py);
      }
    }

    ctx.stroke();
    ctx.setLineDash([]);

    // Draw individual components (if enabled)
    if (showComponents.checked && n <= 10) {
      for (let k = 1; k <= n; k++) {
        const hue = (k / n) * 360;
        ctx.strokeStyle = `hsla(${hue}, 70%, 50%, 0.3)`;
        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
        ctx.beginPath();

        for (let i = 0; i <= samples; i++) {
          const x = (i / samples) * xRange;
          let y = 0;

          if (type === 'square') {
            y = (4 / Math.PI) * Math.sin((2 * k - 1) * x) / (2 * k - 1);
          } else if (type === 'triangle') {
            const sign = (k - 1) % 2 === 0 ? 1 : -1;
            y = (8 / (Math.PI * Math.PI)) * sign * Math.sin((2 * k - 1) * x) / Math.pow(2 * k - 1, 2);
          } else if (type === 'sawtooth') {
            const sign = k % 2 === 0 ? 1 : -1;
            y = -(2 / Math.PI) * sign * Math.sin(k * x) / k;
          }

          const px = padding + (i / samples) * graphWidth;
          const py = centerY - (y * graphHeight / 4);

          if (i === 0) {
            ctx.moveTo(px, py);
          } else {
            ctx.lineTo(px, py);
          }
        }

        ctx.stroke();
      }
    }

    // Draw approximation
    ctx.strokeStyle = '#3498DB';
    ctx.lineWidth = 3;
    ctx.beginPath();

    let errorSum = 0;

    for (let i = 0; i <= samples; i++) {
      const x = (i / samples) * xRange;
      const target = targetWave(x, type);
      const approx = fourierApproximation(x, n, type);
      const px = padding + (i / samples) * graphWidth;
      const py = centerY - (approx * graphHeight / 4);

      errorSum += Math.pow(target - approx, 2);

      if (i === 0) {
        ctx.moveTo(px, py);
      } else {
        ctx.lineTo(px, py);
      }
    }

    ctx.stroke();

    // Calculate RMS error percentage
    const rmsError = Math.sqrt(errorSum / samples);
    const errorPercent = (rmsError / 2) * 100; // Normalize to percentage
    errorDisplay.textContent = `${errorPercent.toFixed(2)}%`;

    // Labels
    ctx.fillStyle = '#2C3E50';
    ctx.font = '13px DM Sans';
    ctx.fillText('0', padding - 10, centerY + 5);
    ctx.fillText('2π', padding + graphWidth / 2 - 10, height - padding + 20);
    ctx.fillText('4π', width - padding - 15, height - padding + 20);

    // Legend
    ctx.fillStyle = '#BDC3C7';
    ctx.fillText('Target', width - padding - 60, padding + 20);
    ctx.fillStyle = '#3498DB';
    ctx.fillText('Approximation', width - padding - 120, padding + 40);
  }

  function animate() {
    if (!isAnimating) return;

    let terms = parseInt(termsSlider.value);
    terms++;

    if (terms > 50) {
      terms = 1;
      isAnimating = false;
      animateBtn.textContent = 'Animate';
      return;
    }

    termsSlider.value = terms.toString();
    drawFourierSeries();

    setTimeout(() => {
      animationFrame = requestAnimationFrame(animate);
    }, 300);
  }

  termsSlider.addEventListener('input', drawFourierSeries);
  waveType.addEventListener('change', drawFourierSeries);
  showComponents.addEventListener('change', drawFourierSeries);

  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    isAnimating = false;
    if (animationFrame) {
      cancelAnimationFrame(animationFrame);
    }
    termsSlider.value = '1';
    waveType.value = 'square';
    showComponents.checked = false;
    animateBtn.textContent = 'Animate';
    drawFourierSeries();
  });

  animateBtn.addEventListener('click', () => {
    if (isAnimating) {
      isAnimating = false;
      if (animationFrame) {
        cancelAnimationFrame(animationFrame);
      }
      animateBtn.textContent = 'Animate';
    } else {
      isAnimating = true;
      termsSlider.value = '1';
      animateBtn.textContent = 'Stop Animation';
      animate();
    }
  });

  window.addEventListener('resize', drawFourierSeries);

  // Initial draw
  drawFourierSeries();
</script>
